title: Canada Three Month Interbank Rate (Cdor)
description: Canada Three Month Interbank Rate (Cdor) was at 4.64 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Canada averaged 2.97 percent from 1992 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 8.95 percent in November of 1992 and a record low of 0.43 percent in October of 2009. In Canada, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Canada Overnight Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: CIBC World Markets
